==English==
===Noun===
'''[[aleph]]-[[one]]'''
#(''mathematics'') The second of the [[transfinite]] [[cardinal number]]s; corresponds to the number of [[real number]]s; also the order of all the numbers in a plane (and therefore the [[complex number]]s); or of any n-dimensional [[manifold]]. Georg Cantor's diagonal proof showed that they could never be put in one-to-one correspondence with the integers, and are therefore not ''countable'' or ''denumerable''.
